com.calendarfx.model

Class Interval

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.calendarfx.model.Interval

  • public final class Interval
extends Object
    A class used for storing the time interval and time zone of an entry.
    See Also:
    Entry.setInterval(Interval)

    • Constructor Detail

      • Interval

        public Interval()
        Constructs a new time interval with start and end dates equal to LocalDate.now(). The start and end times will be set to LocalTime.now() and LocalTime.now() plus one hour. The time zone will be set to ZoneId.systemDefault().

      • Interval

        public Interval(LocalDate startDate,
                LocalTime startTime,
                LocalDate endDate,
                LocalTime endTime)
        Constructs a new time interval with the given start and end dates / times. The time zone will be initialized with ZoneId.systemDefault().
        Parameters:
        startDate - the start date (e.g. Oct. 3rd, 2015)
        startTime - the start time (e.g. 10:45am)
        endDate - the end date
        endTime - the end time

      • Interval

        public Interval(LocalDateTime startDateTime,
                LocalDateTime endDateTime)
        Constructs a new time interval with the given start and end dates / times. The time zone will be initialized with ZoneId.systemDefault().
        Parameters:
        startDateTime - the start date and time (e.g. Oct. 3rd, 2015, 6:15pm)
        endDateTime - the end date and time

      • Interval

        public Interval(ZonedDateTime zonedStartDateTime,
                ZonedDateTime zonedEndDateTime)
        Constructs a new time interval with the given start and end zoned dates / times. The time zone will be initialized with the time zone of the start date time. However, if the zone ID of the second argument is different then an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        zonedStartDateTime - the start date and time (e.g. Oct. 3rd, 2015, 6:15pm)
        zonedEndDateTime - the end date and time
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if two different time zones are used

      • Interval

        public Interval(LocalDateTime startDateTime,
                LocalDateTime endDateTime,
                ZoneId zoneId)
        Constructs a new time interval with the given start and end dates / times and time zone.
        Parameters:
        startDateTime - the start date and time (e.g. Oct. 3rd, 2015, 6:15pm)
        endDateTime - the end date and time
        zoneId - the time zone

      • Interval

        public Interval(LocalDate startDate,

        Parameters:
        startDate - the start date (e.g. Oct. 3rd, 2015)
        startTime - the start time (e.g. 10:45am)
        endDate - the end date
        endTime - the end time
        zoneId - the time zone
